<BaseLayout title="Ferret Care Guide" description="Learn how to care for a ferret: habitat, diet, health, and legal considerations.">
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ferret Care Guide</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">Ferrets are playful and curious mammals requiring interactive environments and regular veterinary care.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Habitat</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Provide a spacious cage with multiple levels, hammocks, and tunnels. Allow supervised time outside the cage for exercise.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Diet</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Feed a high-protein ferret kibble supplemented with occasional treats like cooked eggs or meat. Avoid sugary fruits and vegetables.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Health</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Schedule yearly veterinary exams. Spay or neuter your ferret and vaccinate against distemper. Ferrets are prone to adrenal disease and insulinoma.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Legality</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Ferrets are illegal in some cities and require permits in others. See <a href="/laws/new-jersey" class="text-primary font-bold underline">state laws</a> for details.</p>
